urlLink Alzheimer's Disease Cases in US Expected to Top 13 Million by 2050 : "Alzheimer's Disease Cases in US Expected to Top 13 Million by 2050                                                                                                NEW YORK (Reuters Health) Aug 19 - Unless preventive measures are discovered, the number of US citizens with Alzheimer's disease (AD) will increase nearly three fold in the next half century, new research suggests.    The findings, which are published in the August issue of the Archives of Neurology, are based on prevalence estimates made using the 2000 Census."